  <mainDescription>A horizontal collection of viewpoints that capture multiple sets of concerns for a set of stakeholders, and define&#xD;
solutions to those concerns. The set of defined viewpoints describe the complete architecture of a system at a specific&#xD;
level of abstraction and for specific sets of stakeholders. The three perspectives defined in UAM are Business, Logical,&#xD;
and Technical. There is also&amp;nbsp;the Scope definition that is a very simple context model and not a perspective and is&#xD;
included in the Business Perspective. &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Enterprise architecture is&amp;nbsp;describe using three perspectives that are horizontal views of the IT architecture.&#xD;
    Each perspective&amp;nbsp;is in turn divided into four views called &quot;aspects&quot;. These three perspectives are:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../UAM/guidances/termdefinitions/uam_perspective_business_FB485ABA.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_pH7UgMJKEeKSedlRPHdUIQ&quot;>Perspective: Business&lt;/a>&lt;strong>&amp;nbsp;-&lt;/strong> a set of viewpoints that&#xD;
        collectively define a complete model for the business, at the business level and using business terminology;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../UAM/guidances/termdefinitions/uam_perspective_logical_326F52C.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_0RzzAMJKEeKSedlRPHdUIQ&quot;>Perspective: Logical&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;a set of viewpoints that collectively&#xD;
        define a complete model of the system at the logical level;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../UAM/guidances/termdefinitions/uam_perspective_technical_9964F56F.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_2e3gcMJKEeKSedlRPHdUIQ&quot;>Perspective: Technical&lt;/a> &amp;nbsp;- similar to the Business and Logical Perspectives,&#xD;
        the Technical Perspective is a set of viewpoints that collectively define a complete model of the system at the&#xD;
        technical level.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The other dimension to defining an IT architecture are the different &quot;aspects&quot;, see: &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../UAM/guidances/termdefinitions/uam_aspects_C681E8E1.html&quot; guid=&quot;_2D_igNZSEdyTWqLy4FSCdg&quot;>Architecture&#xD;
    Aspects&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
